defs.value: WindowAttributes { dimensions, min_dimensions, max_dimensions, monitor, title, visible, transparent, decorations, multitouch, resize_callback }
defs.docs: Attributes to use when creating a window.

defs.name: dimensions
defs.docs:
The dimensions of the window. If this is `None`, some platform-specific dimensions will be
 used.

defs.name: min_dimensions
defs.docs: The minimum dimensions a window can be, If this is `None`, the window will have no minimum dimensions (aside from reserved).

defs.name: max_dimensions
defs.docs: The maximum dimensions a window can be, If this is `None`, the maximum will have no maximum or will be set to the primary monitor's dimensions by the platform.

defs.name: monitor
defs.docs: If `Some`, the window will be in fullscreen mode with the given monitor.

defs.name: title
defs.docs: The title of the window in the title bar.

defs.name: visible
defs.docs: Whether the window should be immediately visible upon creation.

defs.name: transparent
defs.docs:
Whether the the window should be transparent. If this is true, writing colors
 with alpha values different than `1.0` will produce a transparent window.

defs.name: decorations
defs.docs: Whether the window should have borders and bars.

defs.name: multitouch
defs.docs:
[iOS only] Enable multitouch, see [UIView#multipleTouchEnabled]
 (https://developer.apple.com/library/ios/documentation/UIKit/Reference/UIView_Class/#//apple_ref/occ/instp/UIView/multipleTouchEnabled)

defs.name: resize_callback
defs.docs:
A function called upon resizing, necessary to receive resize events on Mac and possibly
 other systems.

defs.name: Numeric
defs.docs: Cocoa and X11 use a numeric identifier to represent a monitor.

defs.name: Name
defs.docs: Win32 uses a Unicode string to represent a monitor.

defs.name: Unavailable
defs.docs: Other platforms (Android) don't support monitor identification.

defs.name: NativeMonitorId
defs.docs:
Native platform identifier for a monitor. Different platforms use fundamentally different types
 to represent a monitor ID.
